# CODEOWNERS — path-ownership map.
#
# NOTE: Owner handles are intentionally left as inert TODO placeholders.
# Non-existent @org/team handles make CODEOWNERS invalid and cause
# `require_code_owner_reviews` to become unsatisfiable, which would BLOCK every PR.
# Until real teams/users exist, these rules are commented out so the file stays
# valid and CI remains runnable. Replace `OWNER_PLACEHOLDER` with real GitHub
# team/user handles (e.g. @your-org/rust-team) and uncomment to activate enforcement.
#
# Last matching pattern wins.

# CI/CD definitions (security-critical):
# /.github/                 @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER
# /.github/workflows/       @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER
# /.github/CODEOWNERS       @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER
# /.github/ci-builder-image @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER

# Canonical clinical engine (Rust = source of truth):
# /backend/                 @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER

# Presentational/advisory only:
# /frontend/                @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER

# Generated IPC surface (drift-guarded in ci-contract):
# /shared/                  @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER

# Clinical Truth Layer (requires clinical-governance sign-off):
# /tests/clinical-truth/    @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER

# IPC contract / parity:
# /tests/contracts/         @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER

# Visual regression (non-blocking):
# /tests/visual/            @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER

# Real-shell E2E smoke:
# /tests/e2e/               @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER

# Testing governance, sign-off policy, macOS gate:
# /docs/testing/            @OWNER_PLACEHOLDER
